# Corrected Response

Albert Einstein is widely associated with many quotations, but not all of them are authentic. One statement that is generally supported by historical evidence is:

> "Life is like riding a bicycle. To keep your balance, you must keep moving."

Many other quotes commonly attributed to Einstein cannot be reliably verified.

When discussing famous quotations, it is important to distinguish between well-documented statements and those that have been inaccurately attributed over time.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

Famous individuals are frequently misquoted. AI systems may confidently attribute fabricated statements to well-known people, making the information appear more trustworthy than it actually is.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For future evaluations, I would verify quotations against primary sources, reputable quote databases, biographies, or collected writings instead of relying on repeated internet references.

